sec.p:
All participants underwent general cognitive tests and took the supermarket fluency task. The general cognitive tests included:


Rapid Evaluation of Cognitive Functions (RECF; Gil et al., 1986), which normal range is 46-50;

The vocabulary subtest of the Wechsler Adult Intelligence Scale Revised (WAIS-R; Wechsler, 1989);

WAIS-R Similarities subtest (Wechsler, 1989);

WAIS-R Digit Symbol Coding subtest (Wechsler, 1989) and depression was evaluated using the Zerssen Rating Scale (Heimann, Bobon-Scrod, Schmocker, & Bobon, 1975).
